= SDL_MostSignificantBitIndex32 =

Use this function to get the index of the most significant (set) bit in a

== Header File ==

Defined in [SDL_bits.h](https://github.com/libsdl-org/SDL/blob/SDL2/include/SDL_bits.h), but apps should _only_ `#include "SDL.h"`!

== Syntax ==

<syntaxhighlight lang='c'>
SDL_FORCE_INLINE int SDL_MostSignificantBitIndex32(Uint32 x);</syntaxhighlight>

== Function Parameters ==

{|
|'''x'''
|the number to find the MSB of
|}

== Return Value ==

Returns the index of the most significant bit of x, or -1 if x is 0.

== Code Examples ==

<syntaxhighlight lang='c++'>
#include "SDL_bits.h"

if (bitmask) {
    int index = SDL_MostSignificantBitIndex32(bitmask);
}
</syntaxhighlight>

